WEBVTT

00:45.380 --> 00:48.514
[wind howling]

00:50.851 --> 00:55.721
<i> - This cold isn't something</i>
<i> we can tame.</i>

00:55.723 --> 00:58.190
<i> We did this to our climate.</i>

00:58.259 --> 01:00.593
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

01:00.661 --> 01:04.597
<i> Now only the Earth herself</i>
<i> can restart her warm heart.</i>

01:08.335 --> 01:12.471
<i> I believe we can find</i>
<i> her pulse again.</i>

01:12.539 --> 01:14.740
<i> And my biggest fear...</i>

01:14.809 --> 01:17.676
<i> isn't dying out here.</i>

01:17.745 --> 01:20.479
<i> It's that the cold-hearted</i>
<i> among us will crush that hope</i>

01:20.547 --> 01:22.748
<i> before I can prove it.</i>

01:22.750 --> 01:24.851
<i> ♪ </i>

01:47.775 --> 01:50.843
[engine buzzing]

01:55.650 --> 01:59.919
[engine revving]

01:59.987 --> 02:01.754
[sighs]

02:06.593 --> 02:09.662
[grunting]

02:12.333 --> 02:14.534
<i> ♪ </i>

02:37.492 --> 02:39.559
[beeping]

02:40.895 --> 02:42.962
All right, all right.

02:46.701 --> 02:48.935
<i> ♪ </i>

03:09.724 --> 03:12.258
[grunting]

03:26.741 --> 03:28.741
<i> ♪ </i>

03:33.748 --> 03:36.882
<i> Breslauer Research Station.</i>

03:36.884 --> 03:38.150
<i> The temperature</i>

03:38.219 --> 03:41.620
<i> is minus 122.6 Celcius.</i>

03:41.689 --> 03:44.690
<i> I'm 11,000 feet</i>
<i> above sea level,</i>

03:44.692 --> 03:47.693
<i> dangling</i>
<i> from a thin umbilical.</i>

03:47.695 --> 03:49.762
[panting]

03:49.830 --> 03:52.831
<i> Many miles from Snowpiercer...</i>

03:52.900 --> 03:55.834
<i> 1,034 cars long.</i>

03:55.903 --> 03:59.071
[breathing heavily]

04:02.309 --> 04:05.244
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

04:05.312 --> 04:07.246
<i> ♪ </i>

04:27.334 --> 04:29.068
[door closes]

04:29.136 --> 04:32.271
<i> [unsettling music]</i>

04:32.339 --> 04:34.173
<i> ♪ </i>

05:07.174 --> 05:11.510
[breathing heavily]

05:11.579 --> 05:13.513
<i> ♪ </i>

05:43.544 --> 05:46.545
There you are.

05:46.614 --> 05:48.881
Okay.

05:48.949 --> 05:51.284
[grunts]

05:55.690 --> 05:58.624
[breathing quickens]

05:58.693 --> 06:00.593
<i> ♪ </i>

06:02.029 --> 06:04.563
<i> - Mommy?</i>
<i> Are you there?</i>

06:04.632 --> 06:07.566
<i> There's a monster</i>
<i> under my bed.</i>

06:07.634 --> 06:09.034
<i> Mommy.</i>

06:09.103 --> 06:11.636
<i> Where are you?</i>
<i> Mommy?</i>

06:11.638 --> 06:13.739
<i> Mommy, there's a monster.</i>

06:16.443 --> 06:17.776
<i> Mom?</i>

06:17.845 --> 06:21.647
- [breathing heavily]

06:21.716 --> 06:23.916
All right. All right.

06:23.985 --> 06:25.852
<i> ♪ </i>

06:34.729 --> 06:36.862
[grunts]

06:36.931 --> 06:39.865
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

06:39.934 --> 06:41.834
<i> ♪ </i>

06:51.478 --> 06:53.478
[pneumatic hiss]

06:53.548 --> 06:56.415
<i> I found the bodies</i>
<i> of two of the scientists</i>

06:56.483 --> 06:59.352
<i> stationed here</i>
<i> at the Freeze...</i>

06:59.420 --> 07:03.022
<i> one male, shot in the head...</i>

07:03.090 --> 07:06.892
<i> the other a woman</i>
<i> who slit her wrists.</i>

07:08.029 --> 07:11.531
<i> Must've been a grim place</i>
<i> to face the end of the world.</i>

07:12.900 --> 07:16.369
<i> But at first light,</i>
<i> I have to power it back up,</i>

07:16.437 --> 07:19.572
<i> patch my batteries</i>
<i> into the solar array.</i>

07:19.640 --> 07:21.106
<i> Then I'll go back down</i>

07:21.175 --> 07:22.975
<i> for the sled</i>
<i> I left behind with my rations.</i>

07:23.044 --> 07:26.111
[wind howling]

07:26.113 --> 07:29.114
<i> [suspenseful music]</i>

07:29.116 --> 07:30.983
<i> ♪ </i>

07:50.537 --> 07:53.406
[gasping]

08:09.090 --> 08:10.957
<i> ♪ </i>

08:33.981 --> 08:37.250
[beeping]

08:44.792 --> 08:47.726
Okay.

08:47.795 --> 08:49.662
[groans]

08:51.599 --> 08:53.566
[grunts]

08:57.805 --> 08:59.972
[grunts]

09:03.344 --> 09:06.545
[machinery whirring]

09:06.613 --> 09:09.081
[exhales sharply]

09:12.887 --> 09:14.654
Thank you.

09:16.757 --> 09:19.659
[rumbling]

09:27.969 --> 09:32.037
[wind howling]

09:32.106 --> 09:34.006
<i> ♪ </i>

09:52.126 --> 09:54.360
[sighs]

10:03.938 --> 10:07.406
<i> [ethereal music]</i>

10:07.475 --> 10:08.941
<i> - In the old time,</i>

10:09.009 --> 10:11.610
<i> the future</i>
<i> seemed multifaceted.</i>

10:11.612 --> 10:16.482
<i> We had careers, families,</i>
<i> personal aspirations,</i>

10:16.550 --> 10:19.418
<i> places to go, friends to see,</i>
<i> bucket lists--</i>

10:19.420 --> 10:23.355
<i> the hum of human dreams</i>
<i> we took for granted.</i>

10:23.424 --> 10:25.491
<i> But we were sleepwalking,</i>

10:25.559 --> 10:26.893
<i> just one step away</i>

10:26.961 --> 10:30.429
<i> from trading</i>
<i> all those possible futures</i>

10:30.498 --> 10:34.366
<i> for the shared fate</i>
<i> of the Freeze.</i>

10:34.435 --> 10:37.636
- I thought I'd find you here.

10:37.638 --> 10:40.239
- It's a beautiful thing
we've created.

10:40.308 --> 10:45.778
- Ah. Depends how we
define "created."

10:45.846 --> 10:50.383
Well, I suppose you might
deserve a little credit.

10:52.653 --> 10:54.186
You're the glue.

10:54.255 --> 10:56.722
You put all Snowpiercer's
pieces together.

10:56.791 --> 10:59.725
She's just as much yours
as she is mine.

10:59.794 --> 11:02.861
And you will never hear me
repeat that in public.

11:02.930 --> 11:05.131
[cork pops]

11:05.199 --> 11:08.000
- Whatever your investors
need to hear, Joseph.

11:08.068 --> 11:10.136
- Oh, they heard it.

11:10.204 --> 11:13.071
My "Engine Eternal."

11:13.141 --> 11:16.608
- Depends how
we define "eternal."

11:16.677 --> 11:18.945
- [chuckles]
Now, now...

11:19.013 --> 11:20.879
let's not ruin the moment.

11:20.881 --> 11:22.881
- That's not possible,

11:22.951 --> 11:25.151
because now...

11:25.219 --> 11:27.419
we finally get to drive her.

11:27.488 --> 11:29.688
[exhales deeply]

11:29.757 --> 11:32.758
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

11:32.827 --> 11:35.161
[pneumatic hiss]

11:38.098 --> 11:40.733
[sighs]
Okay.

11:42.637 --> 11:45.037
[scoffs]

11:45.105 --> 11:47.039
<i> ♪ </i>

11:52.112 --> 11:54.046
[sighs]

11:54.114 --> 11:56.048
<i> ♪ </i>

12:09.930 --> 12:12.465
[scoffs]

12:15.069 --> 12:17.603
<i> - Mommy? Where's the food?</i>

12:17.672 --> 12:19.705
<i> Did you go to the store?</i>

12:22.276 --> 12:24.010
<i> I'm hungry.</i>

12:24.078 --> 12:26.045
<i> ♪ </i>

12:30.685 --> 12:33.352
- Ah, so that's where
that arm went.

12:33.354 --> 12:35.221
<i> ♪ </i>

12:38.693 --> 12:40.426
[chuckles]

12:40.494 --> 12:42.461
<i> ♪ </i>

12:44.098 --> 12:45.698
You're exhausted.

12:45.766 --> 12:47.566
Or is it this thin mountain air

12:47.568 --> 12:49.802
that's playing tricks
on your mind?

12:51.639 --> 12:53.572
- [exhales deeply]

12:53.574 --> 12:56.242
- So, with your supplies
under that avalanche,

12:56.310 --> 12:59.578
all you have left
is one ration pack...

12:59.647 --> 13:03.649
one bag of sweeties from Ben...

13:03.718 --> 13:05.384
and an arm.

13:05.386 --> 13:06.853
- I'll manage without the arm.

13:06.921 --> 13:11.224
- Really?
That seems a bit optimistic.

13:12.727 --> 13:14.526
According to the logbooks,

13:14.595 --> 13:16.995
our fine young cannibals
out there

13:16.997 --> 13:19.732
were climate scientists.

13:19.800 --> 13:22.735
They came out
at the start of the Freeze

13:22.803 --> 13:26.538
looking for a way
to survive CW-7--

13:26.607 --> 13:29.007
well, the effects of it.

13:29.009 --> 13:31.677
Apparently
they didn't succeed,

13:31.746 --> 13:34.514
though she did hang on
for five months.

13:36.284 --> 13:39.685
- I only have to make it one.

13:39.754 --> 13:40.953
- Hmm.

13:42.623 --> 13:47.159
- [panting]

13:47.227 --> 13:49.161
<i> ♪ </i>

14:01.842 --> 14:04.310
[beeping]

14:04.378 --> 14:07.313
[electronics whirring]

14:07.381 --> 14:09.348
<i> ♪ </i>

14:21.261 --> 14:23.061
<i> [unsettling music]</i>

14:23.131 --> 14:25.598
- Afraid to look upon
your predecessors' visage?

14:25.666 --> 14:27.333
- Just don't want to see it.

14:27.401 --> 14:31.203
- Because they had
a little girl.

14:31.271 --> 14:35.073
You've acquired a...
sentimental streak, Melanie.

14:35.143 --> 14:36.675
You're a lot more useful

14:36.744 --> 14:39.545
when you're
naive and ambitious.

14:39.613 --> 14:41.279
- Snowpiercer
should be releasing

14:41.281 --> 14:43.015
the first of her weather
balloons

14:43.083 --> 14:45.083
right about now.

14:45.153 --> 14:48.086
I am...

14:48.088 --> 14:52.090
patched into
the climate-modeling program.

14:52.092 --> 14:53.826
Just need to link
to the balloon

14:53.894 --> 14:55.962
<i> from the radio tower.</i>

14:58.899 --> 15:01.233
Feed it enough data points
to extrapolate a model.

15:01.301 --> 15:03.702
- [echoing] Well, if anyone
can kludge together

15:03.704 --> 15:07.239
a heuristic climate model,
it's you, my dear.

15:07.307 --> 15:11.177
Shame you have to rely
on Ben, though, hmm?

15:11.245 --> 15:12.645
And his balloons.

15:12.713 --> 15:13.846
And that Spaniard.

15:13.914 --> 15:14.847
[laughing]
Come on.

15:14.915 --> 15:16.382
- You know Javi's Colombian.

15:16.450 --> 15:18.450
- Oh, well,
perhaps that's where

15:18.519 --> 15:20.586
you'll find our fabled Eden.

15:20.655 --> 15:23.189
- And he didn't know we were
stealing the train from you.

15:23.257 --> 15:25.591
- Hmm.

15:25.660 --> 15:27.726
- Actually, we were two days
down the track

15:27.795 --> 15:30.363
before he figured it out.

15:32.600 --> 15:35.267
- This is nice, isn't it?

15:35.336 --> 15:37.603
Jousting?

15:37.672 --> 15:40.539
[echoing]
Keeps your mind off the hunger.

15:40.541 --> 15:43.643
[laptop chirping]

16:05.566 --> 16:10.236
[laptop beeping]

16:10.304 --> 16:11.838
[computer chimes]

16:11.906 --> 16:14.573
Yes!

16:14.575 --> 16:17.009
Yes!

16:18.847 --> 16:21.380
- Seems a long way to Eden.

16:21.449 --> 16:23.049
- It's a start.

16:23.117 --> 16:24.984
<i> ♪ </i>

16:32.393 --> 16:35.561
[device beeping]

16:41.469 --> 16:44.403
<i> [unsettling music]</i>

16:44.472 --> 16:46.305
<i> ♪ </i>

16:48.876 --> 16:51.010
- Lost your biscuit?

16:55.549 --> 16:57.750
- I must've eaten it.

16:57.818 --> 17:02.354
- [echoing] I know
you don't believe that.

17:02.423 --> 17:04.757
- No.

17:04.825 --> 17:08.427
I didn't eat that cracker.

17:08.429 --> 17:11.497
- Which begs the question...

17:11.565 --> 17:13.031
who did?

17:13.033 --> 17:15.367
Perhaps our cannibals
are hungry.

17:15.436 --> 17:19.105
Either that, or you're
cracking up, Engineer.

17:21.109 --> 17:23.242
<i> - Tell me you</i>
<i> aren't really doing this.</i>

17:23.311 --> 17:27.446
With everything else we need,
you're working on your brothel?

17:27.448 --> 17:29.782
- Not a brothel.
A Nightcar!

17:29.850 --> 17:32.585
- This train is now an ark
for humanity,

17:32.653 --> 17:34.520
not your personal indulgences.

17:34.589 --> 17:36.054
- Can't it be both?

17:36.124 --> 17:37.523
[chuckles]

17:37.591 --> 17:39.525
Art onstage...

17:39.594 --> 17:42.228
and entertainment in the back.

17:43.864 --> 17:46.064
It sustains the soul,
Melanie...

17:46.134 --> 17:48.935
and it's a release valve
to keep everyone under control.

17:49.003 --> 17:51.003
- The resources
that you're wasting on this

17:51.071 --> 17:55.107
could sustain 20 more people
that we're going to need.

17:56.410 --> 17:58.611
Ticketing says you removed
half of my geneticists

17:58.679 --> 17:59.812
from the passenger list.

17:59.880 --> 18:02.014
- We have
more important priorities.

18:02.082 --> 18:02.949
- Like what?

18:03.017 --> 18:05.684
Like...your security?

18:05.686 --> 18:08.687
- I promised you--
all guns will be confiscated

18:08.689 --> 18:10.088
and thrown from the train.

18:10.158 --> 18:11.890
But the Jackboots
will keep order.

18:11.960 --> 18:16.495
3,000 souls stuffed
into a 10-mile steel tube--

18:16.564 --> 18:17.964
you think they're all
gonna suddenly

18:18.032 --> 18:21.033
start singing "Kumbaya"?

18:21.101 --> 18:24.971
- I think that if we are going
to save humankind,

18:25.039 --> 18:26.772
we need people
who actually know

18:26.841 --> 18:28.674
how to save humankind.

18:30.244 --> 18:32.911
- How many?
- Six geneticists...

18:32.913 --> 18:35.047
and next of kin--12 total.

18:35.115 --> 18:36.915
Just cut 12 Jackboots.

18:36.985 --> 18:39.652
- I'll cut six.
- [scoffs]

18:39.720 --> 18:42.521
Joseph, please...

18:42.523 --> 18:45.992
There are gonna be more
important things than order.

18:46.060 --> 18:49.161
- Nothing's more important
than order.

18:50.798 --> 18:54.333
- Do you even believe
in any of this?

18:54.402 --> 18:58.070
- Clearly, I've been
working you too hard...

18:58.138 --> 19:02.274
which is why I will forgive
what you just said.

19:02.343 --> 19:07.346
Snowpiercer has only one
Head Engineer--her creator.

19:07.348 --> 19:08.681
She runs on my order.

19:08.749 --> 19:11.884
And if you can't accept that,
then...

19:11.952 --> 19:14.153
your family can stay behind.

19:15.756 --> 19:17.956
Is that clear?

19:18.026 --> 19:19.425
[chuckles]
You can't--

19:19.493 --> 19:21.827
you can't sugarcoat
the end of the world, Melanie.

19:21.896 --> 19:23.830
Not everything's going
to be fine,

19:23.898 --> 19:27.165
but I promise you...

19:27.235 --> 19:29.167
you will survive.

19:29.237 --> 19:31.137
<i> ♪ </i>

19:34.308 --> 19:36.642
- Thank you, Joseph.

19:42.583 --> 19:45.751
[computers humming]

19:49.858 --> 19:53.459
<i> - It's been ten days</i>
<i> since I arrived.</i>

19:53.527 --> 19:55.928
<i> If I had food...</i>
<i> [chuckles]</i>

19:55.996 --> 19:58.330
<i> This would be</i>
<i> a glowing report.</i>

19:58.399 --> 20:00.799
<i> With each new probe,</i>
<i> the system has more data,</i>

20:00.868 --> 20:03.469
<i> and I coax a climate model.</i>

20:03.538 --> 20:07.005
<i> The picture's</i>
<i> far from complete.</i>

20:07.007 --> 20:09.942
<i> Now the question...</i>

20:10.010 --> 20:11.610
<i> is whether I can survive</i>
<i> long enough</i>

20:11.679 --> 20:13.345
<i> to finish painting it.</i>

20:13.414 --> 20:16.348
[wind howling]

20:16.417 --> 20:19.551
<i> [unsettling music]</i>

20:19.620 --> 20:21.454
<i> ♪ </i>

20:39.507 --> 20:41.641
- Hunger's a bitch, ain't it?

20:42.910 --> 20:44.176
You're getting a little taste

20:44.244 --> 20:47.646
of what you did to us
back in the Tail.

20:47.648 --> 20:49.915
Not to rub it in.

20:49.984 --> 20:51.650
- No, you're rubbing it in.

20:51.652 --> 20:53.719
- Yeah, I am.

20:53.788 --> 20:56.455
Those bodies might have
a little freezer burn,

20:56.524 --> 21:00.258
but I wouldn't let that
put you off.

21:00.260 --> 21:02.194
No judgment here.

21:02.263 --> 21:04.263
- I'm not resorting
to cannibalism.

21:04.332 --> 21:06.532
- Give yourself another week
with no food.

21:06.600 --> 21:08.701
- I've got food.

21:17.277 --> 21:19.678
[distant clatter]

21:19.747 --> 21:22.681
<i> [suspenseful music]</i>

21:22.750 --> 21:24.650
<i> ♪ </i>

21:36.631 --> 21:39.698
- [squeaking]

21:39.767 --> 21:41.767
- [gasps]

21:41.836 --> 21:43.636
<i> ♪ </i>

21:54.849 --> 21:58.017
[grunting]

22:04.058 --> 22:06.192
<i> - You know</i>
<i> this is crazy, right?</i>

22:06.260 --> 22:07.860
- Yep.

22:07.928 --> 22:11.397
- It's been seven years.
How could anything be alive?

22:11.465 --> 22:12.999
- It shouldn't be.

22:13.067 --> 22:15.467
- So either something
did survive out there,

22:15.536 --> 22:17.870
which is a miracle, or...

22:17.938 --> 22:19.405
- I'm losing it?

22:19.473 --> 22:22.074
- You said it, not me.

22:22.142 --> 22:24.076
<i> ♪ </i>

22:30.351 --> 22:32.351
- Oh! Very nice.

22:32.353 --> 22:34.620
Looks like something a Tailie
would've cooked up.

22:34.689 --> 22:37.657
- That's what
I'm talking about.

22:44.765 --> 22:48.835
[panting]

22:48.903 --> 22:52.638
[wind howling]

22:56.176 --> 22:59.511
I've been thinking
about the three bodies I found.

22:59.580 --> 23:01.047
- Torrid affair.

23:01.115 --> 23:03.249
Arthur was the first to go.

23:03.317 --> 23:06.719
The fellow with the bullet
in his brainpan.

23:06.787 --> 23:08.454
The other two got rid of him.

23:08.522 --> 23:11.189
- He was her husband.
- Really?

23:11.191 --> 23:15.327
- The woman who killed herself.
- How'd you find that out?

23:15.396 --> 23:18.330
- He's the guy
on the screensaver.

23:18.399 --> 23:20.733
- Oh, I like that twist.

23:20.801 --> 23:24.136
- Maybe he got sick.
- Yes.

23:24.204 --> 23:27.205
She and the other fellow
knew he was a goner.

23:27.275 --> 23:29.742
Every day he lingered on
was another day

23:29.810 --> 23:31.810
he was consuming food
they needed.

23:31.879 --> 23:34.613
- [softly] So they put him
out of his misery.

23:34.615 --> 23:36.214
- Shot to the head.

23:36.284 --> 23:39.385
She sacrificed him, Melanie...

23:41.622 --> 23:45.057
Like you did to me.
- [sighs]

23:48.562 --> 23:51.063
She made the right decision.

23:52.700 --> 23:55.067
- I knew you'd say that.

23:57.505 --> 23:59.438
- What else could she do?

24:01.910 --> 24:04.643
[crowd shouting indistinctly]

24:04.712 --> 24:06.712
<i> [suspenseful music]</i>

24:06.781 --> 24:08.180
<i> - There's thousands of 'em.</i>

24:08.249 --> 24:10.849
<i> We need reinforcements</i>
<i> at the main gate.</i>

24:10.918 --> 24:12.050
- Where's Javi?

24:12.052 --> 24:13.452
- Engine room.

24:15.656 --> 24:17.790
How did they find out
departure time?

24:17.858 --> 24:21.594
- It's 45 below and getting
colder by the minute, you know.

24:21.662 --> 24:25.197
[phone rings]
Where else are they gonna go?

24:25.266 --> 24:27.599
It's Engineer Cavill again.

24:27.668 --> 24:29.936
Has the transport
with my family arrived yet?

24:30.004 --> 24:33.472
I need to know the moment
they're on the train.

24:33.541 --> 24:35.674
- What the hell's going on
downtrain?

24:35.743 --> 24:37.209
- Wait.
- I told you.

24:37.277 --> 24:39.077
- Can you get me Tail Command?
- Both of you!

24:39.147 --> 24:40.746
More security!
- Hold on.

24:40.815 --> 24:43.081
- We're about to be overrun
before we leave the station.

24:43.083 --> 24:44.350
- Commander Grey's on the line.

24:44.418 --> 24:46.084
- Right.

24:46.154 --> 24:47.954
Is that you,
old Blood and Thunder?

24:48.022 --> 24:49.421
What's the story back there?

24:49.490 --> 24:51.423
- The perimeter fence
is holding, sir,

24:51.492 --> 24:52.691
but more just keep coming.

24:52.760 --> 24:53.892
<i> We fired live rounds,</i>

24:53.962 --> 24:55.561
<i> but it won't hold much longer.</i>

24:55.629 --> 24:59.097
- If they break through...
you unleash hell on them.

24:59.167 --> 25:01.367
You do whatever it takes
to hold them back.

25:01.435 --> 25:03.101
Is that clear?
<i> - Yes, sir.</i>

25:03.103 --> 25:05.771
<i> All necessary force.</i>

25:05.840 --> 25:08.106
- Last train
to Clarksville, people.

25:08.176 --> 25:09.642
- My family isn't on board yet.

25:09.710 --> 25:11.910
- And we still need 30 minutes

25:11.912 --> 25:14.647
to finish
cycling up the engine, sir.

25:14.715 --> 25:17.516
[man shouting indistinctly
outside]

25:17.518 --> 25:19.518
- Who the hell is this?

25:19.587 --> 25:21.920
<i> [tense music]</i>

25:21.990 --> 25:25.791
- We're scientists!
We have tickets!

25:25.860 --> 25:30.729
[rat squeaking frantically]

25:30.731 --> 25:32.832
[trap clacks]

25:41.676 --> 25:42.808
- [gasps]

25:42.877 --> 25:44.743
You're real.
- Yes!

25:44.745 --> 25:47.013
Way to go, Mel.

25:47.081 --> 25:51.017
I know a great recipe for her.

25:51.085 --> 25:52.351
Him.

25:53.754 --> 25:55.555
- I have a better idea.

25:57.692 --> 26:00.492
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

26:00.561 --> 26:02.395
<i> ♪ </i>

26:12.106 --> 26:15.041
[rat squeaking]

26:15.109 --> 26:16.976
<i> ♪ </i>

26:58.018 --> 27:01.187
[grunting]

27:07.227 --> 27:10.096
[saw whirring]

27:10.164 --> 27:12.031
<i> ♪ </i>

27:36.857 --> 27:39.492
Frickin' amazing.

27:43.598 --> 27:45.598
[gasps]

27:47.001 --> 27:49.468
- It's a geothermal vent.

27:53.207 --> 27:55.141
- The warmth kept them alive?

27:55.209 --> 27:58.410
- That fissure looks like
it has a fresh crack in it.

27:58.479 --> 28:00.879
Must have opened up
in the Freeze.

28:00.949 --> 28:03.282
- I bet you're right.

28:03.351 --> 28:06.018
I guess the rats came
with the people,

28:06.086 --> 28:08.154
but they found it first.

28:08.222 --> 28:10.156
- But then you found them.

28:10.224 --> 28:13.091
- [exhales sharply]
It's a miracle.

28:13.161 --> 28:15.561
- [scoffs]

28:15.629 --> 28:17.530
It's life, Mom.

28:21.402 --> 28:24.604
[Melanie humming]

28:32.813 --> 28:34.413
- Yum.
- [chuckles]

28:34.481 --> 28:36.481
- Seven years
hiding and procreating

28:36.551 --> 28:39.418
in a steam vent, and now
straight into our stomachs.

28:39.486 --> 28:41.420
- Yeah, well...

28:41.488 --> 28:43.756
zero regrets.

28:43.824 --> 28:46.291
- I like your chances
better now.

28:46.361 --> 28:48.093
The vent can supplement
your heat

28:48.095 --> 28:50.896
and allow more power
for your databases.

28:50.898 --> 28:53.566
- Doing everything I can.

28:53.634 --> 28:56.202
Still a lot of track
between us.

28:57.638 --> 29:00.906
- What will you do
without your sled to meet us?

29:00.975 --> 29:04.309
- I'll walk
back to the track...

29:04.379 --> 29:08.047
pack a battery
and the hard drive on the sled.

29:08.115 --> 29:10.115
I could make it there and back
if I had to.

29:10.117 --> 29:13.219
[wind howling outside]

29:22.863 --> 29:24.129
- Mom?

29:24.131 --> 29:27.133
I think I understand now...

29:28.736 --> 29:31.704
Why you had to leave me
in Chicago.

29:38.746 --> 29:41.680
<i> [tense music]</i>

29:41.749 --> 29:42.748
<i> ♪ </i>

29:42.817 --> 29:44.149
<i> - What are your orders, sir?</i>

29:44.218 --> 29:46.151
[crowd shouting indistinctly]

29:46.153 --> 29:48.087
They say they're ticketed.

29:48.155 --> 29:49.755
<i> They've got chips!</i>

29:49.824 --> 29:51.891
- They are my geneticists.

29:51.959 --> 29:53.893
You agreed to have them...
- What?

29:53.961 --> 29:55.694
- On board,
and we need them.

29:55.763 --> 29:57.696
- I agreed you could have six.

29:57.765 --> 29:59.498
Right now
we need six Jacks more.

29:59.566 --> 30:03.035
- I am not going
without all of them, Joseph.

30:03.104 --> 30:04.837
You know what? We don't have
time to discuss it.

30:04.906 --> 30:07.773
Let's just
get everyone on board.

30:07.842 --> 30:09.975
- You're right.

30:09.977 --> 30:11.710
There's no time.

30:11.779 --> 30:13.913
Terminate them.

30:13.981 --> 30:16.782
[group screaming]

30:16.784 --> 30:19.785
<i> [dark music]</i>

30:19.787 --> 30:21.654
<i> ♪ </i>

30:21.856 --> 30:23.722
Never forget, Melanie.

30:23.791 --> 30:26.292
The train runs on my order.

30:28.129 --> 30:31.130
Estimated time of departure?

30:31.198 --> 30:33.666
- 28 minutes.
- Good.

30:33.734 --> 30:35.468
Now I'm going downtrain.

30:35.536 --> 30:39.138
And we're going to open fire
on the main gate, too.

30:39.206 --> 30:42.141
You just finish
the damn cycle-up...

30:42.209 --> 30:43.676
and be ready to depart.

30:43.744 --> 30:46.411
- She'll be ready.

30:46.413 --> 30:47.813
- Good.

30:49.484 --> 30:52.217
We'll take the Jeep.

30:52.287 --> 30:54.019
- [stammers]

30:54.088 --> 30:55.988
<i> ♪ </i>

30:59.294 --> 31:01.861
[sighs]

31:04.031 --> 31:08.301
[device beeping]

31:08.369 --> 31:11.270
[laptop beeping]

31:17.178 --> 31:21.314
[laptop chirps, chimes]

31:21.382 --> 31:25.718
[distant clatter]

31:25.786 --> 31:28.854
Come on.

31:28.856 --> 31:30.856
[wind howling]

31:30.858 --> 31:33.592
[metal rattling]

31:33.661 --> 31:35.194
Ping.

31:40.001 --> 31:42.001
[distant clang]

31:44.539 --> 31:46.672
[gasps]

31:46.674 --> 31:49.675
<i> [suspenseful music]</i>

31:49.677 --> 31:52.678
[panting]

31:52.680 --> 31:54.547
<i> ♪ </i>

31:59.554 --> 32:02.688
[wind whistling]

32:02.690 --> 32:04.557
<i> ♪ </i>

32:37.658 --> 32:40.325
- You're having quite the day,
aren't you?

32:40.395 --> 32:44.663
Now you've lost
your balloon data.

32:44.732 --> 32:46.866
- No, no, no, no, no!

32:46.934 --> 32:48.267
- I bet you're feeling a bit

32:48.335 --> 32:50.403
like our friend
out in the snow.

32:50.471 --> 32:52.204
You know,
the woman who, uh...

32:52.273 --> 32:53.873
- Oh, shut up.

32:53.941 --> 32:58.477
- Suicide in that manner,
I've--I've grown to respect...

32:58.545 --> 33:00.679
depending on the circumstances,
of course.

33:00.748 --> 33:02.882
Sometimes it--it transforms.

33:02.950 --> 33:05.751
- What are you
even talking about?

33:05.820 --> 33:07.352
- Ah, you wouldn't understand.

33:07.422 --> 33:09.222
I've no respect
for her, though.

33:09.290 --> 33:12.357
She left her child behind,
you know.

33:12.359 --> 33:14.827
- She did it
to be with her child,

33:14.895 --> 33:17.830
because she thought that
they would be reunited.

33:17.898 --> 33:19.698
- Sentimentality.

33:19.767 --> 33:22.167
Same reason she couldn't eat
her husband.

33:22.236 --> 33:24.569
And for what?
Her mission failed.

33:24.571 --> 33:28.974
She sacrificed her family,
her humanity, everything,

33:28.976 --> 33:31.710
just like you.

33:31.779 --> 33:34.379
- This mission is not done.

33:34.449 --> 33:36.249
Alex is meeting me
at the cold lock.

33:36.317 --> 33:39.051
- Ah, yes. Get back to Alex.

33:39.120 --> 33:41.053
Save her from the monster.

33:41.122 --> 33:43.856
[scoffs]
- I'll catch another rat.

33:43.924 --> 33:47.526
I'll make it two more weeks,
you sack of shit.

33:47.595 --> 33:50.395
- I find it telling,
this notion

33:50.465 --> 33:54.500
you're such a better human
than me.

33:56.203 --> 33:59.205
I saved the daughter
you left behind.

34:00.541 --> 34:03.676
Perhaps a-a little gratitude
is in order?

34:03.744 --> 34:05.678
- [yells]

34:05.746 --> 34:10.183
[exhaling deeply]

34:13.687 --> 34:16.622
[wind howling]

34:16.690 --> 34:19.891
<i> [tense music]</i>

34:19.893 --> 34:21.761
<i> ♪ </i>

34:55.329 --> 34:57.597
- [grunts]

34:59.533 --> 35:02.201
<i> They should be</i>
<i> with four bodyguards.</i>

35:02.270 --> 35:03.803
<i> My par--</i>

35:03.871 --> 35:06.005
<i> my parents are elderly.</i>

35:06.073 --> 35:07.939
[crowd shouting indistinctly]

35:07.941 --> 35:10.209
- Drop those, now!

35:10.277 --> 35:12.612
- Yes, my--my daughter
is eight.

35:12.680 --> 35:17.349
<i> If they're not checked in,</i>
<i> I need you to look for them.</i>

35:17.351 --> 35:20.686
Hello! Hello!

35:22.089 --> 35:23.623
[receiver clatters]

35:23.691 --> 35:25.958
I don't think they're here yet.

35:26.027 --> 35:29.228
<i> - Engine, come in.</i>
<i> Engine, come in.</i>

35:29.297 --> 35:33.365
<i> [static crackling]</i>
<i> Engine, come in.</i>

35:33.367 --> 35:34.834
- This is the Engine.

35:34.902 --> 35:36.568
<i> - I've lost contact</i>
<i> with Commander Grey.</i>

35:36.638 --> 35:38.237
<i> I'm driving uptrain</i>
<i> to see him.</i>

35:38.306 --> 35:40.840
<i> As soon as I get off,</i>
<i> we leave.</i>

35:40.908 --> 35:43.709
- Roger that.
Ready to leave in six minutes.

35:46.113 --> 35:47.847
We can roll in one minute, Mel.

35:47.915 --> 35:49.448
- [scoffs]
I'm going down there.

35:49.517 --> 35:51.450
- You have to make the call
to go.

35:51.519 --> 35:52.784
- Alex might be trying
to get on board.

35:52.786 --> 35:54.386
- You can't get
off this train, Mel.

35:54.388 --> 35:55.855
I am not leaving you here.
- Ben, let me go.

35:55.923 --> 35:57.523
- I have to go.
- We can't let that monster

35:57.591 --> 35:59.859
be in charge of what's left
of humanity.

35:59.927 --> 36:02.328
You want to steal the train
and save the future?

36:02.396 --> 36:04.263
We have to go now.

36:07.201 --> 36:10.002
[distant gunfire]

36:10.071 --> 36:13.005
[distant crowd screaming]

36:13.074 --> 36:14.974
<i> ♪ </i>

36:31.425 --> 36:32.824
<i> - All aboard.</i>

36:32.826 --> 36:36.496
<i> All ticketed passengers,</i>
<i> please board.</i>

36:36.564 --> 36:40.099
<i> Snowpiercer departs</i>
<i> at precisely 0000 hours.</i>

36:40.167 --> 36:42.034
<i> ♪ </i>

36:45.306 --> 36:46.972
Release the brake.

36:47.041 --> 36:49.775
[keys clacking]
- Disengaging brakes.

36:52.980 --> 36:55.514
<i> - Snowpiercer departs</i>
<i> in ten...</i>

36:55.583 --> 36:59.184
<i> nine, eight, seven,</i>

36:59.253 --> 37:00.586
<i> six, five...</i>

37:00.654 --> 37:02.454
- Off the train!
Throw 'em off the train!

37:02.456 --> 37:05.725
<i> - Three, two, one...</i>

37:05.793 --> 37:07.393
<i> departure.</i>

37:07.461 --> 37:09.395
<i> ♪ </i>

37:12.266 --> 37:14.200
[voice breaking]
Engaging the Engine.

37:14.268 --> 37:17.203
<i> [somber music]</i>

37:17.271 --> 37:19.205
<i> ♪ </i>

37:31.218 --> 37:32.884
[sobs softly]

37:32.886 --> 37:35.087
[whispering]
Forgive me.

37:35.089 --> 37:36.956
<i> ♪ </i>

37:42.029 --> 37:43.963
Forgive me.

37:44.031 --> 37:45.898
<i> ♪ </i>

37:52.039 --> 37:54.974
[wind howling]

37:55.042 --> 37:58.044
[metal rattling]

38:00.381 --> 38:02.615
[grunts]

38:03.985 --> 38:06.018
[groans]

38:15.463 --> 38:18.564
[grunting]

38:26.207 --> 38:28.708
[suit alarm beeping]

38:31.613 --> 38:34.546
<i> [suspenseful music]</i>

38:34.616 --> 38:36.516
<i> ♪ </i>

38:36.884 --> 38:38.918
[grunts]

38:40.554 --> 38:42.822
Shit.

38:42.890 --> 38:44.857
<i> ♪ </i>

39:01.108 --> 39:04.010
[computer beeping]

39:05.579 --> 39:08.314
<i> [hopeful music]</i>

39:08.382 --> 39:11.717
[crying]

39:11.785 --> 39:13.385
Yeah.

39:13.454 --> 39:16.255
It's working. It's working.

39:16.324 --> 39:18.191
<i> ♪ </i>

39:28.336 --> 39:30.536
[sobs]

39:32.406 --> 39:34.473
[laughs]

39:36.277 --> 39:40.112
Time to turn around
and hurry back, Snowpiercer.

39:45.820 --> 39:48.754
- [panting]

39:48.823 --> 39:51.757
[wind howling]

39:51.826 --> 39:54.360
[grunting]

39:54.428 --> 39:57.763
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

39:57.832 --> 39:59.699
<i> ♪ </i>

40:31.131 --> 40:32.531
<i> [radio clicks]</i>

40:32.533 --> 40:34.066
<i> Snowpiercer.</i>

40:34.134 --> 40:36.735
<i> Snowpiercer, come in.</i>

40:36.737 --> 40:39.305
<i> You should be in range by now.</i>

40:40.274 --> 40:42.941
Do you copy?
It's Melanie.

40:42.943 --> 40:46.412
<i> [static crackling]</i>

40:46.480 --> 40:48.347
<i> ♪ </i>

40:53.354 --> 40:55.087
[radio clicks]

40:55.155 --> 40:58.024
Snowpiercer, Snowpiercer.

40:58.092 --> 40:59.025
Do you copy?

40:59.093 --> 41:02.295
<i> [static crackling]</i>

41:04.098 --> 41:05.698
Snowpiercer.

41:05.766 --> 41:08.835
I'm prepared to rendezvous
for pickup.

41:13.307 --> 41:15.241
[radio clicks]
Ben?

41:15.309 --> 41:18.644
<i> [static crackling]</i>

41:18.713 --> 41:21.179
[radio clicks]
Alex?

41:21.249 --> 41:25.584
<i> [static crackling]</i>

41:25.586 --> 41:27.920
[radio clicks]
I have the climate model.

41:29.390 --> 41:32.458
<i> [static crackling]</i>

41:36.931 --> 41:40.132
[radio clicks]

41:40.200 --> 41:42.401
Allie...

41:42.470 --> 41:45.871
[sighs]

41:45.940 --> 41:47.840
I tried.
[scoffs]

41:49.677 --> 41:52.445
[voice breaking]
I r-really tried.

41:53.814 --> 41:55.081
And...

41:55.149 --> 41:57.950
I thought this time
would be different.

42:00.688 --> 42:03.623
I thought I would get
back to you.

42:04.959 --> 42:06.859
So...

42:08.629 --> 42:10.963
Please forgive me.

42:13.233 --> 42:15.167
<i> [static crackling]</i>

42:15.235 --> 42:18.771
[sighs]

42:18.839 --> 42:20.306
[sighs]

42:20.374 --> 42:24.110
- You gave up everything
for us...

42:24.178 --> 42:25.978
for the world.

42:27.181 --> 42:30.917
[softly] You don't
have to be sorry anymore...

42:30.985 --> 42:33.185
not to me...

42:33.253 --> 42:34.787
not to anyone.

42:34.855 --> 42:39.658
Snowpiercer couldn't have made
it this far without you.

42:39.727 --> 42:44.196
And you and I would never
have gotten this chance.

42:44.264 --> 42:46.198
- Thank you.

42:46.266 --> 42:49.201
<i> [somber music]</i>

42:49.269 --> 42:51.103
<i> ♪ </i>

42:57.611 --> 43:00.546
[crying softly]

43:00.614 --> 43:02.481
<i> ♪ </i>

43:07.555 --> 43:10.489
<i> [static crackling]</i>

43:10.558 --> 43:12.458
<i> ♪ </i>

43:16.364 --> 43:19.599
[rumbling]

43:23.838 --> 43:27.840
[panting]

43:27.908 --> 43:30.776
Snowpiercer.
[gasps]

43:33.648 --> 43:35.982
Snowpiercer!
Do you hear me?

43:36.050 --> 43:39.852
<i> [dramatic music]</i>

43:39.920 --> 43:41.187
Snowpiercer.

43:41.255 --> 43:43.389
You need to slow your roll.

43:43.457 --> 43:45.324
<i> ♪ </i>

43:46.794 --> 43:50.429
You need to slow your roll!
Do you hear me?

43:51.599 --> 43:54.066
Stop!
[electricity crackling]

43:54.134 --> 43:57.936
[brakes squealing]

43:58.006 --> 43:59.906
<i> ♪ </i>

44:08.549 --> 44:12.018
- [muffled]
Mom! Mom!

44:12.086 --> 44:14.053
<i> ♪ </i>

44:19.093 --> 44:22.028
[breathing quickens]

44:22.096 --> 44:24.063
<i> ♪ </i>
